#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:334
msgid ""
"Perry validates the backend/target pairing early: Metal is Apple-only, "
"Vulkan is available on macOS/Linux/Windows/Android/HarmonyOS, and D3D12 is "
"Windows-only. Precompiled shader outputs and resources are copied under "
"`NativeLibraries/<package>/<backend>/` in app bundles."
msgstr ""
"Perry valida la combinación backend/objetivo de manera temprana: Metal es "
"exclusivo de Apple, Vulkan está disponible en "
"macOS/Linux/Windows/Android/HarmonyOS, y D3D12 es exclusivo de Windows. Las "
"salidas de shaders precompilados y los recursos se copian en "
"`NativeLibraries/<package>/<backend>/` dentro de los bundles de la "
"aplicación."

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:339
msgid "6. Update over time"
msgstr "6. Actualizar con el tiempo"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:341
msgid ""
"**A new perry-ffi feature lands**: bump your `Cargo.toml`'s `perry-ffi` "
"version, rebuild prebuilts, tag a new release. Users `bun update` to pick it"
" up. Perry's manifest spec stays at v1 unless the schema changes."
msgstr ""
"**Llega una nueva funcionalidad de perry-ffi**: actualiza la versión de "
"`perry-ffi` en tu `Cargo.toml`, reconstruye los precompilados y etiqueta una"
" nueva versión. Los usuarios ejecutan `bun update` para adoptarla. La "
"especificación del manifiesto de Perry permanece en v1 salvo que cambie el "
"esquema."

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:345
msgid ""
"**A new Perry minor**: same — `perry-ffi`'s semver moves with Perry's minor."
" The git-URL consumption (v0.5.x) means rebuilding against `main` picks it "
"up automatically."
msgstr ""
"**Un nuevo minor de Perry**: igual — el semver de `perry-ffi` avanza con el "
"minor de Perry. El consumo por URL de git (v0.5.x) significa que reconstruir"
" contra `main` lo adopta automáticamente."

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:348
msgid ""
"**Breaking change to the `js_*` surface you exported**: bump your package's "
"major version (`1.0.0` → `2.0.0`). Users who pin a major aren't affected."
msgstr ""
"**Cambio incompatible en la superficie `js_*` que exportaste**: actualiza la"
" versión mayor de tu paquete (`1.0.0` → `2.0.0`). Los usuarios que fijan una"
" versión mayor no se ven afectados."

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:352
msgid "Common patterns"
msgstr "Patrones comunes"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:354
msgid "Async one-shot (HTTP request, DB query)"
msgstr "Operación asíncrona puntual (petición HTTP, consulta a base de datos)"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:371
msgid "\"fetch: {}\""
msgstr ""

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:378
msgid "Sync handle-based class"
msgstr "Clase síncrona basada en handles"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:380
msgid ""
"Use a `handle` descriptor for synchronous resource-style APIs. The native "
"function receives or returns the raw resource pointer as `i64`, while "
"TypeScript callers see only the opaque handle object."
msgstr ""
"Usa un descriptor `handle` para APIs de recursos síncronos. La función "
"nativa recibe o devuelve el puntero de recurso sin procesar como `i64`, "
"mientras que los llamadores de TypeScript solo ven el objeto handle opaco."

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:400
msgid "Event listeners (`.on(event, cb)`)"
msgstr "Listeners de eventos (`.on(event, cb)`)"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:409
msgid "// closure pointers, kept alive by the GC scanner below\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:452
msgid ""
"The GC scanner is **load-bearing**: without it, a malloc-triggered GC "
"between `.on(cb)` and `.emit()` will sweep the closure and the next emit "
"calls freed memory. Always register a scanner if your handles store closure "
"pointers."
msgstr ""
"El scanner de GC es **fundamental**: sin él, un GC activado por malloc entre"
" `.on(cb)` y `.emit()` eliminará el closure y el siguiente emit llamará a "
"memoria liberada. Registra siempre un scanner si tus handles almacenan "
"punteros de closure."

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:457
msgid "When to extend the perry-ffi surface"
msgstr "Cuándo extender la superficie de perry-ffi"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:459
msgid ""
"If your binding genuinely needs something perry-ffi doesn't expose, file an "
"issue against [`PerryTS/perry`](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues) "
"describing:"
msgstr ""
"Si tu binding genuinamente necesita algo que perry-ffi no expone, crea un "
"issue en [`PerryTS/perry`](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues) "
"describiendo:"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:463
msgid "the binding you're writing,"
msgstr "el binding que estás escribiendo,"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:464
msgid "the perry-runtime function/type you'd otherwise reach into,"
msgstr ""
"la función/tipo de perry-runtime que de otro modo utilizarías directamente,"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:465
msgid "why a higher-level perry-ffi entry would generalize."
msgstr ""
"por qué una entrada de perry-ffi de mayor nivel generalizaría el caso."

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:467
msgid ""
"The bar for adding to perry-ffi is high — every helper is a forever "
"commitment — but real wrappers driving real needs is exactly the right "
"input. The recent additions (BigInt + Buffer in v0.5.556, JSON-stringify + "
"event-pump in v0.5.567 followups) all came from specific wrappers needing "
"them."
msgstr ""
"El umbral para añadir algo a perry-ffi es alto — cada helper es un "
"compromiso permanente — pero los wrappers reales que responden a necesidades"
" reales son exactamente el input correcto. Las adiciones recientes (BigInt +"
" Buffer en v0.5.556, JSON-stringify + event-pump en los seguimientos de "
"v0.5.567) surgieron todas de wrappers específicos que los necesitaban."

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:473
msgid ""
"Don't reach into `perry_runtime::*` directly to \"unblock\" your wrapper "
"today — it'll break the next time those internals change."
msgstr ""
"No accedas directamente a `perry_runtime::*` para \"desbloquear\" tu wrapper"
" hoy — se romperá la próxima vez que cambien esos internos."

