#: src/tui/widgets.md:172
msgid ""
"For state + event hooks (the React-shape "
"`useState`/`useInput`/`useApp`/etc.), see [Hooks](hooks.md). For complete "
"worked examples, see [Examples](examples.md)."
msgstr ""
"Para hooks de estado y eventos (`useState`/`useInput`/`useApp`/etc. con "
"forma React), consulta [Hooks](hooks.md). Para ejemplos completos y "
"detallados, consulta [Ejemplos](examples.md)."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:3
msgid ""
"`perry/tui` implements the React-shape hook API on top of a call-site-"
"indexed slot pool. Each `useXxx` call gets the slot at its position in the "
"component body; the run loop resets the index at the top of every frame, so "
"the second render's `useState` at the same position reads back what the "
"first wrote."
msgstr ""
"`perry/tui` implementa la API de hooks con forma React sobre un pool de "
"slots indexados por sitio de llamada. Cada llamada a `useXxx` obtiene el "
"slot en su posición dentro del cuerpo del componente; el bucle de ejecución "
"reinicia el índice al inicio de cada fotograma, de modo que el `useState` "
"del segundo renderizado en la misma posición lee lo que escribió el primero."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:5
msgid ""
"This is the same rule-of-hooks model ink/React use: **call hooks in the same"
" order on every render**. Don't call them inside `if`/loops — the slot index"
" would skew and you'd read the wrong slot. Slot kinds are tagged (`State` / "
"`Effect` / `Memo` / `Ref` / `Focus`); calling `useState` at a position "
"previously used by `useMemo` re-tags the slot rather than corrupting it, but"
" the value resets."
msgstr ""
"Esta es la misma regla de hooks que usan ink/React: **llama a los hooks en "
"el mismo orden en cada renderizado**. No los llames dentro de `if`/bucles — "
"el índice de slot se desajustaría y leerías el slot incorrecto. Los tipos de"
" slot están etiquetados (`State` / `Effect` / `Memo` / `Ref` / `Focus`); "
"llamar a `useState` en una posición usada previamente por `useMemo` "
"reetiqueta el slot en lugar de corromperlo, pero el valor se reinicia."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:7
msgid "`useState(initial)`"
msgstr ""

#: src/tui/hooks.md:9
msgid "Per-frame state cell. Returns `[value, setter]`."
msgstr "Celda de estado por fotograma. Devuelve `[value, setter]`."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:11
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"const [count, setCount] = useState(0);\n"
"// Later, from an input handler:\n"
"setCount(count + 1);\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/tui/hooks.md:17
msgid ""
"The setter writes through to the slot's bits and flips a global "
"`STATE_DIRTY` flag — the run loop sees it after `useInput` drains and "
"immediately re-renders without sleeping."
msgstr ""
"El setter escribe directamente en los bits del slot y activa un flag global "
"`STATE_DIRTY` — el bucle de ejecución lo detecta tras drenar `useInput` y "
"vuelve a renderizar inmediatamente sin dormir."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:19
msgid ""
"Setting the same value twice (bit-identical) is a no-op — `STATE_DIRTY` "
"stays clear and the loop idles. This avoids the \"render storm\" pattern "
"where unconditional `setX(prev)` calls would loop forever."
msgstr ""
"Establecer el mismo valor dos veces (bit a bit idéntico) es una operación "
"nula — `STATE_DIRTY` permanece sin activar y el bucle queda inactivo. Esto "
"evita el patrón de «tormenta de renderizado» donde llamadas incondicionales "
"a `setX(prev)` iterarían indefinidamente."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:21
msgid "Stale-closure gotcha"
msgstr "Problema de closure obsoleto"

#: src/tui/hooks.md:23
msgid ""
"The setter captured by a `useInput` handler reads `value` from **that "
"frame's closure**, not from the slot. If many bytes arrive in one frame "
"(paste, typing fast), the handler fires N times with the same `value`:"
msgstr ""
"El setter capturado por un handler de `useInput` lee `value` desde **el "
"closure de ese fotograma**, no desde el slot. Si llegan muchos bytes en un "
"mismo fotograma (pegar, escribir rápido), el handler se ejecuta N veces con "
"el mismo `value`:"

#: src/tui/hooks.md:25
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"const [n, setN] = useState(0);\n"
"useInput((s) => { if (s === \"+\") setN(n + 1); });\n"
"// User pastes \"+++\" — handler fires 3× with n=0, all three set the slot to 1.\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/tui/hooks.md:31
msgid ""
"If you need a functional setter for this case, use `useRef` as a mirror:"
msgstr ""
"Si necesitas un setter funcional para este caso, usa `useRef` como espejo:"

#: src/tui/hooks.md:33
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"const buf = useRef(\"\");\n"
"const [, redraw] = useState(0);\n"
"useInput((s) => {\n"
"    if (s.length === 1 && s >= \" \" && s <= \"~\") {\n"
"        buf.set(buf.get() + s);     // canonical buffer (no stale capture)\n"
"        redraw(buf.get().length);   // trigger re-render\n"
"    }\n"
"});\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/tui/hooks.md:44
msgid "`useEffect(fn, deps?)`"
msgstr "`useEffect(fn, deps?)`"

#: src/tui/hooks.md:46
msgid ""
"Run a side effect after first render, and again whenever a dep changes."
msgstr ""
"Ejecuta un efecto secundario tras el primer renderizado y de nuevo cada vez "
"que cambia una dependencia."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:48
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"useEffect(() => {\n"
"    // Run-once on mount.\n"
"    fetchInitialData();\n"
"}, []);\n"
"\n"
"useEffect(() => {\n"
"    // Re-run whenever `query` changes.\n"
"    runSearch(query);\n"
"}, [query]);\n"
"\n"
"useEffect(() => {\n"
"    // No deps array → run every render. Rarely what you want.\n"
"});\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/tui/hooks.md:64
msgid ""
"Deps are compared by bit-identity using an FNV-1a hash of the deps' NaN-"
"boxed values. An empty array `[]` hashes to a stable non-zero value, giving "
"the React \"run once\" behaviour; passing no array runs the effect every "
"render."
msgstr ""
"Las dependencias se comparan por identidad de bits usando un hash FNV-1a de "
"los valores NaN-boxed de las deps. Un array vacío `[]` produce un hash "
"estable distinto de cero, dando el comportamiento de React \"ejecutar una "
"vez\"; pasar ningún array ejecuta el efecto en cada renderizado."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:66
msgid ""
"The effect closure runs synchronously inside the component call. Cleanup-on-"
"dep-change (returning a cleanup function) is **not** wired yet — the return "
"value is ignored."
msgstr ""
"El closure del efecto se ejecuta de forma síncrona dentro de la llamada al "
"componente. La limpieza al cambiar dependencias (devolviendo una función de "
"limpieza) **no** está conectada aún — el valor de retorno se ignora."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:68
msgid "`useMemo(fn, deps)`"
msgstr "`useMemo(fn, deps)`"

#: src/tui/hooks.md:70
msgid ""
"Cache the result of `fn()` keyed by `deps`. Same hash convention as "
"`useEffect`."
msgstr ""
"Almacena en caché el resultado de `fn()` indexado por `deps`. Misma "
"convención de hash que `useEffect`."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:79
msgid ""
"Recomputes on first call or when `deps` change. Otherwise returns the cached"
" value."
msgstr ""
"Recalcula en la primera llamada o cuando cambian las `deps`. En caso "
"contrario devuelve el valor en caché."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:81
msgid "`useRef(initial)`"
msgstr "`useRef(initial)`"

#: src/tui/hooks.md:83
msgid ""
"A stable mutable cell that doesn't trigger re-renders. Use for values you "
"want to mutate but don't want to drive the UI."
msgstr ""
"Una celda mutable estable que no dispara re-renders. Úsala para valores que "
"quieras mutar pero que no deben controlar la UI."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:85
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"const renderCount = useRef(0);\n"
"renderCount.set(renderCount.get() + 1);   // does NOT flip STATE_DIRTY\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/tui/hooks.md:90
msgid ""
"`.get()` reads, `.set(v)` writes. Identity is stable across renders — "
"calling `useRef(0)` at the same position returns the same handle every time,"
" so closures captured in `useEffect` / `useInput` always see the latest "
"value."
msgstr ""
"`.get()` lee, `.set(v)` escribe. La identidad es estable entre renders: "
"llamar a `useRef(0)` en la misma posición devuelve el mismo handle cada vez,"
" por lo que los closures capturados en `useEffect` / `useInput` siempre ven "
"el valor más reciente."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:92
msgid ""
"Common pattern: use `useRef` as the canonical buffer for input that gets "
"typed at terminal speed, and pair with a throwaway `useState` to trigger "
"redraws (see the stale-closure gotcha above)."
msgstr ""
"Patrón común: usa `useRef` como buffer canónico para la entrada que se "
"teclea a velocidad de terminal, y combínalo con un `useState` desechable "
"para disparar redraws (ver el problema del stale closure más arriba)."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:94
msgid "`useApp()`"
msgstr "`useApp()`"

#: src/tui/hooks.md:96
msgid "Returns a handle for imperative control of the run loop."
msgstr "Devuelve un handle para el control imperativo del bucle de ejecución."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:98
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"const app = useApp();\n"
"// Later:\n"
"app.exit();                    // tells run() to break at the top of the next iteration\n"
"await app.waitUntilExit();     // blocks until EXIT_FLAG is set (rare; usually `run` itself blocks)\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/tui/hooks.md:105
msgid ""
"The handle is stable — calling `useApp()` on every render returns the same "
"singleton. Wrap it in `useRef` if you want to stash it for a callback that "
"outlives the render."
msgstr ""
"El handle es estable: llamar a `useApp()` en cada render devuelve el mismo "
"singleton. Envuélvelo en `useRef` si quieres guardarlo para un callback que "
"sobreviva al render."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:107
msgid "`useStdout()`"
msgstr "`useStdout()`"

#: src/tui/hooks.md:109
msgid "Terminal dimensions and a raw-write escape hatch."
msgstr "Dimensiones del terminal y un escape hatch de escritura directa."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:111
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"const stdout = useStdout();\n"
"const cols = stdout.columns();    // terminal width in cells (falls back to 80 if not a TTY)\n"
"const rows = stdout.rows();       // height in cells (fallback 24)\n"
"stdout.write(\"raw bytes\\n\");      // bypass the cell-grid diff\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/tui/hooks.md:118
msgid ""
"Use `columns`/`rows` to size dividers, truncate content to fit, or pick a "
"layout direction. `write` is rarely needed — almost everything should go "
"through widgets so the cell-grid diff can render it efficiently."
msgstr ""
"Usa `columns`/`rows` para dimensionar divisores, truncar contenido o elegir "
"una dirección de layout. `write` raramente es necesario — casi todo debería "
"pasar por los widgets para que el diff de la cuadrícula de celdas pueda "
"renderizarlo eficientemente."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:120
msgid "`useFocus(autoFocus, isActive)`"
msgstr "`useFocus(autoFocus, isActive)`"

#: src/tui/hooks.md:122
msgid ""
"Register the calling widget as a focus candidate. Returns `1.0` when this "
"widget is the currently focused one, else `0.0` (treat as truthy/falsy)."
msgstr ""
"Registra el widget que llama como candidato al foco. Devuelve `1.0` cuando "
"este widget es el que tiene el foco actualmente, y `0.0` en caso contrario "
"(tratar como truthy/falsy)."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:124
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"const isFocused = useFocus(1 /* autoFocus */, 1 /* isActive */);\n"
"return Box({ flexDirection: \"row\" }, [\n"
"    Text(\"> \", isFocused ? { color: \"cyan\", bold: true } : { dimColor: true }),\n"
"    Text(\"name input\"),\n"
"]);\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/tui/hooks.md:132
msgid ""
"`autoFocus`: pass `1` for one widget to take focus on first render. "
"Subsequent `useFocus` calls with `autoFocus=1` are ignored once focus has "
"been claimed."
msgstr ""
"`autoFocus`: pasa `1` en un widget para que tome el foco en el primer "
"render. Las llamadas posteriores a `useFocus` con `autoFocus=1` se ignoran "
"una vez que el foco ha sido reclamado."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:133
msgid ""
"`isActive`: pass `0` to remove this widget from the Tab cycle (e.g. a "
"disabled field)."
msgstr ""
"`isActive`: pasa `0` para eliminar este widget del ciclo de Tab (por "
"ejemplo, un campo deshabilitado)."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:135
msgid ""
"Tab and Shift-Tab cycle focus automatically — no boilerplate. The run loop's"
" input drain handles the `\\x09` / `\\x1b[Z` byte sequences before "
"forwarding them to your `useInput` handler."
msgstr ""
"Tab y Shift-Tab ciclan el foco automáticamente — sin código repetitivo. El "
"drenado de entrada del bucle de ejecución gestiona las secuencias de bytes "
"`\\x09` / `\\x1b[Z` antes de reenviarlas a tu handler de `useInput`."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:137
msgid "For imperative focus control, pair with `useFocusManager()`:"
msgstr ""
"Para el control imperativo del foco, combínalo con `useFocusManager()`:"

#: src/tui/hooks.md:139
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"const focus = useFocusManager();\n"
"// Later:\n"
"focus.focusNext();\n"
"focus.focusPrevious();\n"
"focus.focus(id);   // by focus id (1-based, in registration order)\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/tui/hooks.md:147 src/tui/hooks.md:178
msgid "`useInput(handler)`"
msgstr "`useInput(handler)`"

#: src/tui/hooks.md:149
msgid ""
"Register a keypress handler. Called once per byte chunk arriving on stdin, "
"in raw mode."
msgstr ""
"Registra un handler de pulsación de teclas. Se llama una vez por cada "
"fragmento de bytes que llega por stdin en modo raw."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:151
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"useInput((s: string) => {\n"
"    if (s === \"\\x03\") app.exit();               // Ctrl+C\n"
"    if (s === \"\\r\" || s === \"\\n\") onSubmit();   // Enter\n"
"    if (s === \"\\x7f\" || s === \"\\b\") onErase();  // Backspace\n"
"    if (s === \"\\x1b[A\") onUpArrow();            // ANSI up\n"
"    if (s.length === 1 && s >= \" \" && s <= \"~\") onPrintable(s);\n"
"});\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/tui/hooks.md:161
msgid ""
"The `s` argument is the raw byte chunk as a string. ANSI escape sequences "
"like arrow keys arrive as a single chunk (`\\x1b[A`, `\\x1b[B`, `\\x1b[C`, "
"`\\x1b[D`); printable characters as one byte; control codes (Ctrl+C, Tab, "
"Enter, Backspace) as their literal byte."
msgstr ""
"El argumento `s` es el fragmento de bytes en bruto como string. Las "
"secuencias de escape ANSI como las teclas de flecha llegan como un único "
"fragmento (`\\x1b[A`, `\\x1b[B`, `\\x1b[C`, `\\x1b[D`); los caracteres "
"imprimibles como un byte; los códigos de control (Ctrl+C, Tab, Enter, "
"Retroceso) como su byte literal."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:163
msgid ""
"**Tab handling**: Tab (`\\x09`) and Shift-Tab (`\\x1b[Z`) cycle the focus "
"ring _before_ the handler is called. The handler still sees the byte, so you"
" can branch on it if you want custom Tab behaviour — but for the typical "
"\"Tab moves focus\" case the framework already did it."
msgstr ""
"**Gestión del Tab**: Tab (`\\x09`) y Shift-Tab (`\\x1b[Z`) ciclan el anillo "
"de foco _antes_ de llamar al handler. El handler sigue viendo el byte, por "
"lo que puedes ramificar sobre él si quieres un comportamiento de Tab "
"personalizado — pero para el caso típico de \"Tab mueve el foco\" el "
"framework ya lo hizo."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:165
msgid ""
"Only one handler is registered at a time (last `useInput` call wins). For "
"multiple focusable widgets, dispatch from one handler by checking "
"`useFocus`'s return."
msgstr ""
"Solo se registra un handler a la vez (gana la última llamada a `useInput`). "
"Para múltiples widgets enfocables, despacha desde un único handler "
"comprobando el retorno de `useFocus`."

#: src/tui/hooks.md:167
msgid "Equivalence with ink"
msgstr "Equivalencia con ink"

#: src/tui/hooks.md:169
