"\"Failed to fetch\" errors). Any local static server works:"
msgstr ""
"**Nota**: Las aplicaciones que usan `fetch()` u otras APIs de la plataforma "
"web que dependen de un origen real deben servirse mediante HTTP (las URLs "
"file:// se topan con errores CORS / \"Failed to fetch\"). Cualquier servidor"
" estático local funciona:"

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:31
msgid ""
"The `perry-codegen-wasm` crate compiles HIR directly to WASM bytecode using "
"`wasm-encoder`. The output WASM:"
msgstr ""
"El crate `perry-codegen-wasm` compila HIR directamente a bytecode WASM "
"usando `wasm-encoder`. El WASM de salida:"

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:33
msgid ""
"Imports ~280 host functions under the `rt` namespace (string ops, math, "
"console, JSON, classes, closures, promises, fetch, etc.)"
msgstr ""
"Importa ~280 funciones del host bajo el namespace `rt` (operaciones de "
"cadenas, matemáticas, consola, JSON, clases, closures, promesas, fetch, "
"etc.)"

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:34
msgid "Imports user-declared FFI functions under the `ffi` namespace"
msgstr ""
"Importa funciones FFI declaradas por el usuario bajo el namespace `ffi`"

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:35
msgid ""
"Exports `_start`, `memory`, `__indirect_function_table`, and every user "
"function as `__wasm_func_<idx>` (so async function bodies compiled to JS can"
" call back into WASM)"
msgstr ""
"Exporta `_start`, `memory`, `__indirect_function_table` y cada función de "
"usuario como `__wasm_func_<idx>` (para que los cuerpos de funciones async "
"compilados a JS puedan llamar de vuelta a WASM)"

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:37
msgid ""
"The NaN-boxing scheme matches the native `perry-runtime` — f64 values with "
"STRING_TAG/POINTER_TAG/INT32_TAG — so the same value representation is used "
"across native and WASM targets. The JS bridge wraps every host import with "
"bit-level reinterpretation so f64 NaN-boxed values pass through the BigInt-"
"based JS↔WASM i64 boundary intact (BigInt(NaN) would otherwise throw)."
msgstr ""
"El esquema NaN-boxing coincide con el `perry-runtime` nativo — valores f64 "
"con STRING_TAG/POINTER_TAG/INT32_TAG — de modo que se usa la misma "
"representación de valores en los targets nativos y WASM. El puente JS "
"envuelve cada importación del host con reinterpretación a nivel de bits para"
" que los valores NaN-boxed en f64 pasen intactos por el límite i64 JS↔WASM "
"basado en BigInt (de lo contrario, BigInt(NaN) lanzaría una excepción)."

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:41
msgid ""
"**Full TypeScript language**: classes (with constructors, methods, "
"getters/setters, inheritance, fields), async/await, closures (with "
"captures), generators, destructuring, template literals, generics, enums, "
"try/catch/finally"
msgstr ""
"**Lenguaje TypeScript completo**: clases (con constructores, métodos, "
"getters/setters, herencia, campos), async/await, closures (con capturas), "
"generadores, destructuring, template literals, genéricos, enums, "
"try/catch/finally"

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:42
msgid ""
"**Module system**: cross-module imports, top-level `const`/`let` (promoted "
"to WASM globals), circular imports"
msgstr ""
"**Sistema de módulos**: importaciones entre módulos, `const`/`let` de nivel "
"superior (promovidos a globales WASM), importaciones circulares"

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:43
msgid ""
"**Standard library**: String/Array/Object methods, Map/Set, JSON, Date, "
"RegExp, Math, Error, URL/URLSearchParams, Buffer, Promise (with "
"`.then`/`.catch`/`.allSettled`/`.race`/`.any`/`.all`)"
msgstr ""
"**Biblioteca estándar**: métodos de String/Array/Object, Map/Set, JSON, "
"Date, RegExp, Math, Error, URL/URLSearchParams, Buffer, Promise (con "
"`.then`/`.catch`/`.allSettled`/`.race`/`.any`/`.all`)"

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:44
msgid ""
"**Async**: `async`/`await` (compiled to JS Promises), "
"`setTimeout`/`setInterval`, `fetch()` with full request options (method, "
"headers, body)"
msgstr ""
"**Async**: `async`/`await` (compilado a Promises de JS), "
"`setTimeout`/`setInterval`, `fetch()` con opciones completas de solicitud "
"(method, headers, body)"

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:45
msgid ""
"**Threading**: `perry/thread` `parallelMap`/`parallelFilter`/`spawn` via Web"
" Worker pool with one WASM instance per worker (see "
"[Threading](../threading/overview.md))"
msgstr ""
"**Threading**: `perry/thread` `parallelMap`/`parallelFilter`/`spawn` "
"mediante un pool de Web Workers con una instancia WASM por worker (ver "
"[Threading](../threading/overview.md))"

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:46
msgid ""
"**DOM-based UI**: every widget in `perry/ui` (`VStack`, `HStack`, `ZStack`, "
"`Text`, `Button`, `TextField`, `Toggle`, `Slider`, `ScrollView`, `Picker`, "
"`Image`, `Canvas`, `Form`, `Section`, `NavigationStack`, `Table`, "
"`LazyVStack`, `TextArea`, etc.) maps to a DOM element with flexbox layout. "
"State bindings (`bindText`/`bindSlider`/`bindToggle`/`bindForEach`/...) work"
" via reactive subscribers."
msgstr ""
"**UI basada en DOM**: cada widget de `perry/ui` (`VStack`, `HStack`, "
"`ZStack`, `Text`, `Button`, `TextField`, `Toggle`, `Slider`, `ScrollView`, "
"`Picker`, `Image`, `Canvas`, `Form`, `Section`, `NavigationStack`, `Table`, "
"`LazyVStack`, `TextArea`, etc.) se mapea a un elemento DOM con diseño "
"flexbox. Los enlaces de estado "
"(`bindText`/`bindSlider`/`bindToggle`/`bindForEach`/...) funcionan mediante "
"suscriptores reactivos."

#: src/platforms/wasm.md:47
msgid ""
"**System APIs**: `localStorage`\\-backed preferences/keychain, dark mode "
"detection (`prefers-color-scheme`), Web Notifications, clipboard, file "
"open/save dialogs, File System Access API, Web Audio capture"
msgstr ""
"**APIs del sistema**: preferencias/keychain respaldadas por `localStorage`, "
"detección de modo oscuro (`prefers-color-scheme`), Notificaciones Web, "
"portapapeles, diálogos de apertura/guardado de archivos, File System Access "
"API, captura de audio web"

