#: src/container/containers.md:163
msgid "Container naming"
msgstr "Nomenclatura de contenedores"

#: src/container/containers.md:165
msgid ""
"The default name is `{md5(image)[0..8]}-{random_hex8}` — a stable "
"8-character hash of the image plus a per-call random suffix. This is fine "
"for one-off `run()` calls but makes containers hard to find later unless you"
" set `name:` explicitly. **For anything you'll re-target later (with "
"`inspect`, `logs`, `exec`, etc.), set `name:` upfront.**"
msgstr ""
"El nombre por defecto es `{md5(image)[0..8]}-{random_hex8}` — un hash "
"estable de 8 caracteres de la imagen más un sufijo aleatorio por llamada. "
"Esto es adecuado para llamadas `run()` puntuales, pero dificulta encontrar "
"los contenedores más adelante a menos que establezcas `name:` "
"explícitamente. **Para cualquier cosa que vayas a referenciar posteriormente"
" (con `inspect`, `logs`, `exec`, etc.), define `name:` desde el principio.**"

#: src/container/containers.md:171
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"const handle = await run({\n"
"  image: \"alpine:3.19\",\n"
"  name: \"build-helper\",   // ← stable handle\n"
"  cmd: [\"sh\", \"-c\", \"echo 'hi from build-helper'\"],\n"
"  rm: true,\n"
"});\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"const handle = await run({\n"
"  image: \"alpine:3.19\",\n"
"  name: \"build-helper\",   // ← stable handle\n"
"  cmd: [\"sh\", \"-c\", \"echo 'hi from build-helper'\"],\n"
"  rm: true,\n"
"});\n"
"```"

#: src/container/containers.md:180
msgid "Backend introspection"
msgstr "Introspección del backend"

#: src/container/containers.md:202
msgid ""
"`getBackend()` is synchronous and returns the canonical backend name "
"(`\"docker\"`, `\"podman\"`, `\"apple/container\"`, etc.). It will perform a"
" synchronous in-place probe on first call so the result is always the live "
"name; calls after the first hit a cached `OnceLock` and return instantly."
msgstr ""
"`getBackend()` es síncrono y devuelve el nombre canónico del backend "
"(`\"docker\"`, `\"podman\"`, `\"apple/container\"`, etc.). Realiza una sonda"
" síncrona en el lugar en la primera llamada para que el resultado sea "
"siempre el nombre activo; las llamadas posteriores usan un `OnceLock` en "
"caché y retornan instantáneamente."

#: src/container/containers.md:208
msgid ""
